<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="123" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,347,1262,1288]" box="[151,347,1262,1288]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,347,1262,1288]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="22" pageNumber="123" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,347,1262,1288]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">
The 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,347,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName box="[207,267,1262,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Neodiogmites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanei">lanei</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1333,1505]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">
This group of species is characterized by: veins R 
<number box="[726,734,1348,1362]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123" value="4.0">4</number>
–R 
<number box="[766,774,1348,1362]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123" value="5.0">5</number>
less than twice length of R 
<number box="[1092,1100,1348,1362]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123" value="5.0">5</number>
–M 
<number box="[1139,1147,1348,1362]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123" value="1.0">1</number>
; postpedicel greater than twice length of scape and pedicel combined; palpus without visible segmentation between first and second segments. Only three specimens of this group are known (
<typeStatus box="[822,922,1408,1433]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[981,1078,1409,1433]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1120,1211,1408,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Neodiogmites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanei">
<emphasis box="[1120,1211,1408,1432]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">N. lanei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<typeStatus box="[1270,1368,1408,1433]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Neodiogmites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tauauna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">N. tauauna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and it was not possible to dissect 
<typeStatus box="[689,737,1445,1469]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">type</typeStatus>
specimens. However, palpal characters distinguish it from congeners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
